items.title: Jeanine Pirro picked Trump as interim top federal prosecutor in D.C.

items.title: Robert Prevost is first American pope: Leo XIV

items.title: Trump calls Robert Prevost's election as first U.S. pope 'such an honor'
items.description: Robert Francis Prevost took the papal name Leo XIV after his election as the first American-born pope in the history of the Roman Catholic Church.

items.title: Crypto regulation bill fails to advance in the Senate
items.description: Several Democrats who previously voted for the bill abruptly backed out, but the final vote wasn't close to the 60 needed to advance.

items.title: Trump says a rate cut would be like 'jet fuel' for markets, but Powell doesn't want to do it
items.description: The Fed on Wednesday voted to keep its benchmark interest rate in a range of 4.25% to 4.5%, where it's kept it on hold since December.
